tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured laboratory values are within normal limits for this 85-year-old female patient. No evidence of acute metabolic, renal, or electrolyte disturbances. Glycemic control appears adequate. No laboratory abnormalities detected at this time. Recommend continued routine monitoring as clinically indicated.
